definition.value: A wetness quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's not being covered by a liquid.

value.value: A shape quality in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's curving inward.

definition.value: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being kept below its freezing point.

value.value: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having a three dimensional cavity with a narrow or no opening, and often containing an anatomical substance.
An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's consisting cells.
A cellularity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's consisting of more than one cell.
A quality that inheres in an entire organism or part of an organism.

A shape that inheres in a 2 dimensional entity, such as a cross section or projection of a 3 dimensional entity.
A complete three dimensional shape in which for every line connecting pair of points on the object is within the object. Or: a shape lacking cavities. Contrast: concave.

definition.value: Use this term or an is_a child of this term when the entire shape of the object is known.

value.value: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the degree to which there are subdivisions or offshoots in a bearer entity.

A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's processing the form of a thin plate sheet or layer.

definition.value: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue the bearer's being changed in position.
A quality which inheres in a molecular entity, a single molecule, atom, ion, radical etc.

value.value: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of its constitution.

definition.value: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being roundish, flattish shape, possibly with a slightly angled edge.

definition.value: Becoming flat but not necessarily completely flat.

A shape that inheres in a 3 dimensional entity.
An elasticity which is relatively high.
